Description: ClariFlow is a clinically proven and patented DIY device for men to identify early signs of BPH.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ClariFlow is a clinically proven and patented DIY device for men to identify early signs of BPH. Urologists also get patient referrals through their mobile app. ClariFlow is the first home test for BPH. Developed over 10 years by researchers in Europe and clinically tested around the world including UCLA, ClariFlow lets you test for maximum urinary flow rate, which is one of the indicators of BPH. Simply preorder the kit online here. Itâll get shipped to you in a discreet package. In conjunction with your symptoms checklist, the easy-to-read gauge will tell you if youâre at risk for BPH. BPH is short for Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia. It means that your prostate is enlarged and this may cause problems with you ability to urinate. For example, you may feel that youâre urinating more frequently than before or that youâre unable to urinate completely. Perhaps your urination interferes with your ability to sleep through the night or youâre getting more urinary tract infections. These are all potential signs that you may have BPH. BPH is very common. Half of men over 50 years old experience this condition, as do 75% of men over 80. Even men in their 30s can begin to experience the symptoms, so you or your loved one is far from being alone. Early diagnosis of BPH is really important. Once you and your doctor know that you have BPH, there are medications that you can take to reduce the need for frequent urination and the uncomfortable feelings associated with BPH. Finding out early also reduces the chances that youâll need surgery later on to correct for your symptoms. And lastly, itâs always a good idea to rule out more serious conditions, such as prostate cancer, as soon as you can, because they sometimes present similar symptoms. BPH can be easily treated if diagnosed early. If left untreated, it can lead to urinary tract infections, incontinence, urinary retention, and other unpleasant symptoms. Extreme cases may call for the use of a catheter in order to empty the bladder, or even surgical intervention.

Its products are used in commercial fraud protection, age verification, productivity enhancement, access control, and law enforcement sectors. The company sells its products directly, as well as through resellers and license agreements. Intellicheck Mobilisa, Inc. was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Port Townsend, Washington.

Full Description: We are a online community that is centered around five crucial elements for long term business success: 1.) Business Advice 2.) Leadership Development 3.) Financial Advice 4.) Personal Development 5.) Marketing Advice All five elements will help improve your skill set as a budding entrepreneur. If you are on the fence about starting your own business venture or if you are stagnating with current business goals, we strongly believe in the importance of encouragement. The Woman in Leadership blog community is a place to share your voice and to make it the go-to resource for female small business owners, work at home moms, and start-ups. What is the Mission and Purpose of Woman in Leadership? Our mission is to help you gain the priceless knowledge that is essential for becoming a successful entrepreneur and prominent leader in your industry. Is the Woman in Leadership Online Community Right for Me? The Woman in Leadership name stands for every entrepreneurial woman who is not afraid to pursue her dreams, no matter the obstacle. If this sounds like you, then this is the right place for you!   Whether you are just starting out or are currently established, we provide you with a wealth of inspiration, motivation, financial, and business building advice.  We also offer affordable professional services for you and your growing business. What Professional Services Does Woman in Leadership Offer? The services offered by Woman in Leadership will change as the community continues to grow.  All services have been created to help you stay on the road to success with your home business, online business, startup, or established small business. Our professional services include the following: Consultation (2 Hours Free) Free Business Building Courses Free Marketing Courses Writing Requests (Blog content, ghostwriting, articles, etc.) Social Media Management and Marketing Advertising and Sponsorship Programs   For detailed information about each of the services we provide, just head on over to Our Services page.  ABOUT THE FOUNDER Stacie Walker, the Editor-in-Chief and the company founder, is the the brainchild behind this fabulous community. She officially said good-bye to her corporate job to build her own business from the comfort of her home in 2008. She has NEVER looked back. Stacie loves working with professional leaders and dedicated entrepreneurs in the small business, home business, and online business industries. Known as a success-driven entrepreneur, it has been her mission and purpose to educate you on possessing the correct tools to establish a better business model and to assist you with improving the quality of your personal life.   A top priority of Stacie is to provide a comfortable place for the novice and the experienced entrepreneur to get a bit of inspiration, motivation, and business building strategies for long term success. She believes all of the above elements are essential to improve your skill set as a budding entrepreneur in your industry.

Resort Gems operates an online travel marketplace for vacation hotspots.
Full Description: Formerly RRBO.com, ResortGems.com operates an online marketplace for vacation resorts at amazing deals. The site features over 5,000 individual timeshare properties for rent, often at 30-50% of their standard nightly rates. In addition, via a partnership with World Choice Travel, a division of Travelocity, the site offers access to more than 27,000 hotels and resorts at the same guaranteed low prices.  Timeshare units are denoted by a "gem" icon, and include top providers such as Marriott, Wyndham, Hilton, and Disney. The startup has raised over $1.1 million since inception, with backing from State of Ohio funded initiatives, Ohio TechAngels, and other high net worth individuals. Once a user finds a hotel, resort, or timeshare they like, they can book it online in minutes. Hotels and resorts booked through the Travelocity network are handled in the same way they are on Travelocity. When a timeshare "gem" that has been listed by its owner is booked, all aspects of that transaction are handled by Resort Gems, from payment and contract to the handover of keys. This escrow-like fashion eliminates risk for the consumer, much like StubHub does for tickets. Resort Gems does not charge timeshare owners to list, and makes money by taking a percentage of each timeshare transaction, or via standard partner kickbacks from Travelocity on resorts and hotels provided via their feed of 27,000+ units. The company slogan is... "Stay at a timeshare, without the sales pitch." Resort Gems has been featured in USA Today, Travel + Leisure, Peter Greenberg, Fox 28 News Columbus, and The Columbus Dispatch. On June 8, 2010 they won an international startup competition held by Weblogs & Mahalo founder Jason Calacanis, tying for first place with personal cloud provider Tonido, during meetup #55 on the popular show This Week in Startups.
